article.description: Mount. St. Mary's Md. 74, Fairleigh Dickinson 65
article.headline: Mount. St. Mary's Md. 74, Fairleigh Dickinson 65
article.linkText: Mount. St. Mary's Md. 74, Fairleigh Dickinson 65
article.story: EMMITSBURG, Md. (AP) -- Jeremy Goode nearly had the first triple double in Mount St. Mary's, Maryland, history with 18 points, 10 rebounds and nine assists, and the Mount defeated Fairleigh Dickinson 74-65 Saturday night. Chris Vann had 22 points, Mychal Kearse scored 11 points and Will Holland added 10 for the Mount (8-13, 7-3 Northeast Conference). Cameron Tyler scored 20 points to lead the Knights (9-10, 4-4 NEC). Michael Peeples had 14 and Andre Harris had 11. A 12-2 run gave the Mount a 58-45 lead with about six minutes remaining, but the Knights scored seven straight points to close the gap. With 3:41 to go, the Mount came back with two free throws and a jumpshot to open the lead back to 10.
